**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- `$where` clauses execute JavaScript on the server, enabling arbitrary code execution
- Time-based attacks can extract sensitive data without visible error messages
- Attackers measure response times to determine if conditions are true
- Entire database can be exfiltrated one character at a time
- No authentication bypass needed - just timing measurements

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import com.mongodb.client.MongoClients;
import com.mongodb.client.MongoClient;
