No, directly using user input in HTTP headers is extremely dangerous and enables CRLF (Carriage Return Line Feed) injection attacks. This vulnerability was exploited in CVE-2023-25690 affecting Apache HTTP Server, allowing attackers to perform HTTP request smuggling.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
import javax.servlet.http.*;
import java.io.IOException;

public class RedirectServlet extends HttpServlet {

    @Override
    protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) 
            throws IOException {

        // VULNERABLE: User input directly used in header
        String redirectUrl = request.getParameter("url");

        // Attacker can inject CRLF sequences to add arbitrary headers
        response.setHeader("Location", redirectUrl);
        response.setStatus(HttpServletResponse.SC_MOVED_TEMPORARILY);

        // Also vulnerable in custom headers
        String userAgent = request.getParameter("source");
        response.setHeader("X-Redirect-Source", userAgent);
    }
}
```

**Attack Payload**:
```text
url=http://example.com%0d%0aSet-Cookie:%20sessionId=malicious%0d%0aX-Injected:%20true
```

This decodes to:
```text
http://example.com\r\nSet-Cookie: sessionId=malicious\r\nX-Injected: true
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Attackers can inject arbitrary HTTP headers into the response
- Enables session fixation by injecting Set-Cookie headers
- Can poison web caches with malicious content
- May enable HTTP response splitting for XSS attacks
- Bypasses security controls like CSP by injecting overriding headers

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import javax.servlet.http.*;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.net.URI;
import java.net.URISyntaxException;
import java.util.Set;
import java.util.logging.Logger;

public class SecureRedirectServlet extends HttpServlet {

    private static final Logger logger = Logger.getLogger(SecureRedirectServlet.class.getName());

    // Allowlist of permitted redirect domains
    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_DOMAINS = Set.of(
        "example.com",
        "secure.example.com",
        "www.example.com"
    );

    @Override
    protected void doGet(HttpServletRequest request, HttpServletResponse response) 
            throws IOException {

        String redirectUrl = request.getParameter("url");

        // SECURITY: Validate and sanitize the URL
        String safeUrl = validateAndSanitizeUrl(redirectUrl, request);

        if (safeUrl != null) {
            // Modern servlet containers sanitize headers, but explicit validation is essential
            response.sendRedirect(safeUrl);
            logger.info("Redirect to: " + safeUrl + " from IP: " + request.getRemoteAddr());
        } else {
            logger.warning("Invalid redirect attempt: " + sanitizeForLog(redirectUrl) + 
                          " from IP: " + request.getRemoteAddr());
            response.sendError(HttpServletResponse.SC_BAD_REQUEST, "Invalid redirect URL");
        }
    }

    private String validateAndSanitizeUrl(String url, HttpServletRequest request) {
        if (url == null || url.isEmpty()) {
            return null;
        }

        // CRITICAL: Reject any CRLF characters
        if (containsCRLF(url)) {
            return null;
        }

        try {
            URI uri = new URI(url);
            String host = uri.getHost();

            // Only allow relative URLs or URLs to allowed domains
            if (host == null) {
                // Relative URL - ensure it doesn't start with // (protocol-relative)
                if (url.startsWith("//")) {
                    return null;
                }
                return url;
            }

            // Verify domain is in allowlist
            if (ALLOWED_DOMAINS.contains(host.toLowerCase())) {
                return uri.toString();
            }

        } catch (URISyntaxException e) {
            // Invalid URI
            return null;
        }

        return null;
    }

    private boolean containsCRLF(String input) {
        return input.contains("\r") || input.contains("\n") || 
               input.contains("%0d") || input.contains("%0a") ||
               input.contains("%0D") || input.contains("%0A");
    }

    private String sanitizeForLog(String input) {
        if (input == null) return "null";
        return input.replaceAll("[\\r\\n]", "_").substring(0, Math.min(input.length(), 200));
    }
}
```

**Key Security Controls**:
- **CRLF Detection**: Explicitly checks for CR (\r), LF (\n), and their URL-encoded forms
- **URL Allowlist**: Only permits redirects to pre-approved domains
- **URI Parsing**: Uses java.net.URI for proper URL validation
- **Audit Logging**: Logs all redirect attempts with sanitized inputs

